Supporters at a rally for President Obama in Youngstown, Ohio, in October 2012 encourage early voting. (Matt Rourke/AP)

No matter what nonsense occurs during the next 18 days of the presidential election, it makes no difference to at least 4 million Americans, since they've already voted. If Donald Trump's poll numbers plunge through the basement floor or if Hillary Clinton suddenly stumbles: No matter. For these happy citizens, they don't have to care one iota,
